2d744c87c2c498510f84b5a91dc14ec703d7b022.commit.message:
Rewrite of MurmurHash3Test using random byte data.

Many tests only sparsely check coverage of the processing of byte[]
data. The new tests check all lengths of byte[] data that would generate
trailing bytes of length 0-15.

Checking of the processing of offset bytes is now performed.

Achieve more coverage of IncrementalHash32 using tests for trailing and
leading bytes not forming a 4 byte block.

Reference data is from the Python mmh3 library (which calls the original
c++ source code). Code examples demonstrate how to generate test data.

Adds tests to demonstrate known sign extension bugs.
2d744c87c2c498510f84b5a91dc14ec703d7b022.commit.author.name: aherbert

b5ce7fae5bb6794d41216756f080a087cb956e90.commit.message:
Fully documented MurmurHash3. This attempts no code changes. The highly modified class passes the current tests. mvn clirr:clirr report shows no changes. Default mvn goal passes: mvn clean verify apache-rat:check clirr:check javadoc:javadoc - Documented all public constants. - Documented IncrementalHash32 class. - Added

tags to paragraphs. - Renamed input variables for consistency across all method. - Renamed internal variables in the hash32, 64, 128 methods so the similarities in the methods are obvious. - prefix joavadoc @params and @returns with 'The' consistently - Added code examples for the methods that hash primitives for the equivalent using a ByteBuffer to encode the bytes. - Fix links in the class header. - Documented sign extension bugs in hash32 and hash128. - Documented hash64 is not from the reference code and does not match part of hash128. - Documented hash64 as may be released in a future version. - Refactored combination of bytes to little endian int/long into methods.
b5ce7fae5bb6794d41216756f080a087cb956e90.commit.author.name: aherbert
